name: language_html_data_double_encoded_lt
description: |
  One HTML decode produces the visible text "&lt;", while a second produces
  less-than. This catches applications where storage, templates, client code,
  and DOM APIs each perform an encoding or decoding pass.
format: utf8-strip
decode-as: ascii
tags:
  - "language"
  - "html"
  - "xss"
  - "xss-data"
  - "character-reference"
  - "double-encoding"
  - "double-decoding"
  - "less-than"
---
&amp;lt;
